<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08940</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE COASTAL ENVIRONMENT PROGRAM, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to adopt a comprehensive program to protect our coastal environment and to progress in the nation's goal of sustainable development.

Provides for the organization of Coastal Environment Program into the following components:
a) Coastal habitats and biodiversity - floral and fauna populations; implementation of the 
National Integrated Protected Areas System Act of 1992; mangroves, seagrass and coral reefs;
b) Endangered species - marine turtles, crocodiles, sea snakes, shore birds, whales, sea cows, porpoises;
c) Coastal industries and pollution - regulation, impact, and mitigation;
d) Resource inventory assessment - stocks of ecologically and economically important coastal   pieces;
e) Research and special projects - methodologies to understand coastal environments and their
associated resource systems.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>PICO, PEPITO M.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-01-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON NATURAL RESOURCES ON 2019-02-04</td></tr></table>